args: I've found you at last, Grace!
Because we are old, dear friends!\nYou must have known I would come\nlooking for you when you vanished.
Come, Grace. Let us go back together.
There is nothing for me in the Syndicate.\nNot without him. The only place I wish\nto go to is where he resides now.
But very well! I accept your terms.\nI will abandon the Syndicate with you.
What are you talking about, Parker?\nSurely you are aware of what happens\nto those who leave that organization.
I am aware—and it's a risk I accept.
I have loved you from the moment\nI first set eyes on you.
I know you have lost someone you love\nand are trapped in the depths of grief.
We bear a similar pain, you and I,\nfor I grieve at the loss of a dear friend.
Should we not join our lives in that case?\nA pain shared is a pain halved, after all.
I am sorry, Parker, but I cannot.\nI am simply not strong enough\nto bear the enormity of his loss.
You could if it was shared! With my help!\nCome with me, Grace, and I will show\nyou how to leave that pain behind!
Ah, but I do not want to leave it behind.\nI wish to keep this pain inside me.
When I remember him, my heart aches.\nAnd yet, the only way to free myself from\nthis torment is for his memories to fade.
I do not wish that. Instead, I seek to go\nto him while his memories are yet fresh.
What would he say on hearing such\nthings? Do you think he wants this for you?
Do you think him the kind of man\nwho hoped his love would blindly\nfollow him off into oblivion?
The kind of man who would reject\nhappiness for his beloved if it came\nin a world he no longer inhabited?
Do this for him, Grace.\nCome with me for him!
Hmm? Why are you so flustered?
You are still with the Syndicate. If Aldred\nfinds you, there will be great trouble.
Very well. But think about my proposal,\nwon't you? I will come for an answer soon.
A traveler asking directions. Nothing more.
I wish to be alone for a while.\nYou two should get some rest.

Hey, you do you. But just so you know,
we're crossing that mountain tomorrow.
If you're worn out because you didn't
sleep, I WILL leave you behind.
Be careful, okay? Who knows what kinds\nof things lurk around here at night.
(...What would you have me do, my love?\nAs Parker says, you would never have\ndesired my death to join with yours.)
(And yet, I wonder if you know just how\nempty and shallow a world is once the\nperson you love is no longer in it?)
(I cannot go on in such a state.\nAnd yet...)
Parker. You followed me all the way here.
I told you I would come for your answer.
My answer, Parker, is no.\nI simply cannot do it.
Grace, I know what happened\nin his final moments.
When Tf-997 and Tf-999 escaped,\nyour husband was attacked by Tf-997.
I knew as soon as I saw him that\nhis wounds were beyond healing.
Even so, I tried. As I set in to heal him,\nhe said four words: ＂Take care of Grace.＂
While my love for you is true, I did not\ncome here simply to sate my own desire.
His last wish was for us to be together,\nand I seek only to honor it!
He did. So please, Grace, come with me.\nI cannot live with myself if I let you\nget killed at the hands of that failure!
By failure I take it you mean Aldred?!\nAnd Andromeda as well?!
Why are you upset? They ARE failures—\neveryone at the lab called them such.
...You are a liar, Parker. And your claims\nof my love's last words are also a lie.
Grace, no! What are you saying?!
My love never used the word ＂failure.＂\nNot for them. Instead, he said that we\nwere the failures.
He said that if we researchers had been\nbetter at our jobs, the test subjects would\nnot have had to suffer as they did...
And I agree with him: We stole everything\nfrom them. Their bodies. Their souls.\nThat is a sin WE must bear.
How can you say this about\nmere test subjects?

＂Mere test subjects＂? ＂Failures＂?
No. My husband would never have
wanted me to be with a man who
carried such thoughts as these.
And I, too, cannot love one such as you.\nThat is one thing I can say with certainty.
Oh, Grace. Oh, my dear.\nIf you will not walk beside me...
If you will not obey me, then you are\na traitor who must be disposed of.
You could have been with me, Grace,\nand instead you cast it all aside.\nYou are a hopeless fool.
And you're a selfish piece of crap.
Tf-997! Why are you helping her?!
Oh, I'm not. But one look at those masks,\nand I couldn't hold my arm back.
What are you two doing here?
Perhaps this is a blessing in disguise.\nMy standing with the Syndicate will only\nrise if I also deal with you, Tf-997!
Careful. Your mouth is making promises\nyou can't possibly keep.
Oh, but I can. For you see, your own\nstrength is about to devour you.
With the power of this crystal...
